IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To raise funds to support programs that serve low-income people, heritage programs, and public improvements in Seattle's Pike Place Market.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO RAISE FUNDS TO SUPPORT PROGRAMS THAT SERVE LOW-INCOME PEOPLE, HERITAGE PROGRAMS, AND PUBLIC IMPROVEMENTS IN SEATTLE'S PIKE PLACE MARKET.
IRS990.Desc: Consists of Disbursements to the following Market-related Not-for-profit entities: Pike Market Medical Clinic - Provides low cost or free medical services for elderly and low income residents of the market area and downtown Seattle. $375k Pike Market Senior Center - Provides meals, social work, employment, and housing services for low income seniors of the market area and downtown Seattle. $255k Pike Market Child Care & Preschool - Provides daycare for low income working families in the area. $300k Pike Market Food Bank - Provides food to downtown residents who wouldn't otherwise be able to get food. $160k Food Access Project & Market Fresh Coupons - a food-coupon system for low-income residents to receive farm fresh produce $117,381 Heritage House at the Market - an assisted living program to serve low income and senior downtown residents. $65k

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: In late 2017, the Foundation opened the Market Commons ("the Commons"), located in the new MarketFront. The Commons is a welcoming and inclusive neighborhood center that provides community resources as well as programs and activities in the Market. The Commons expands delivery of social services - both in the scope of services currently offered and in the number of people served by partner agencies.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Safety Net emergency relief for those living/working in and around the Market Community. Grants are paid directly to service provide i.e. utility company, rental agency. $44,252 Small Business Granting Program- Grants paid to Market Business, started as COVID relief, continues. Applications with specific business expenses cited. $350,925

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE PURPOSE OF THE MARKET FUND AND ENDOWMENT FUND IS TO ADDRESS THREATS AND OPPORTUNITIES TO THE PIKE PLACE MARKET AND/OR ITS HUMAN SERVICE AGENCIES. MAINTAIN THE PURCHASING POWER OF THE CURRENT ASSETS AND ALL FUTURE CONTRIBUTIONS. PROVIDE A SOURCE FOR SEED MONEY TO DEVELOP NEW, LOW-INCOME HOUSING PROJECTS IN THE MARKET AREA. SEED DEVELOPMENT OF NEW MARKET HUMAN SERVICE PROJECTS & FUND CAPITAL AND HERITAGE PROJECTS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12C:
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Employees are required to avoid situations that present a conflict of interest or even the appearance of a conflict of interest. If a conflict, or the appearance of a conflict, occurs, employees must make immediate and full disclosure of the situation to their manager. The Pike Place Market PDA, a governmental entity, contributes some services to the Market Foundation. As a result, the Market Foundation is subject to the City of Seattle Code of Ethics and conflict of interest provision, which prohibit personal benefit or profit from the use of PDA property or their position as an employee of the PDA.
